text: Finneas Baird O'Connell (born July 30, 1997), known as Finneas (written in capital letters), is an American singer-songwriter, record producer, and actor. He has written and produced music for various artists, most notably his sister, Billie Eilish. He has won eight Grammy Awards among 13 total nominations. For his work with Eilish, he has won Record of the Year twice in a row, Album of the Year, and Song of the Year. Their song "No Time to Die" from the movie of the same name earned him an Academy Award and another Grammy. == References == Category:1997 births Category:Record producers from California Category:Singer-songwriters from California Category:Singers from Los Angeles Category:Actors from California Category:American television actors Category:American Grammy Award winners Category:21st-century American singer-songwriters Category:American agnostics Category:American movie actors
